commit.message:
Changing previous type comparison to just comparing how json.dumps renders 2 values.
This avoids flagging mismatches between classes which happen to be different but which are JSONified as the same thing.
Flagging type-only changes with DiffBuilder

Test to reproduce:
https://github.com/stefankoegl/python-json-patch/issues/90
https://github.com/stefankoegl/python-json-patch/issues/103

commit.message:
better exception when unable to fully resolve a jsonpointer on add or replace operations

When a "path" jsonpointer in a add or replace operation points to a non-resolvable inner element, raise a JsonPatchConflict with a clear error message rather than a TypeError with an obscure message
